Sweden... you are looking at 31% - 52% income tax for an average earner. The prevalence of Diabetes Type II, Heart Disease, Kidney Disease, mobility problems, millions of undocumented immigrants not to mention a permanent underclass where teenage motherhood is the norm..... You have 330 million people not 20 million.  I'm not saying healthcare for all is wrong, or not doable, it is, but it is an earned right, not a free right by any stretch of the imagination.
